      "code": "# Creating Charts with Chart.js\n\nIn this example, we create a basic **line chart** using Chart.js loaded from a CDN. The chart displays monthly sales data and demonstrates how to set up Chart.js in a browser without any build tools.\n\n### Features:\n- Uses the **UMD version** of Chart.js via CDN.\n- Draws a simple **line chart** with labels and a dataset.\n- Chart is fully **responsive** and includes a **title**",
      "status": "",
      "output": "<h1>Creating Charts with Chart.js</h1>\n<p>In this example, we create a basic <strong>line chart</strong> using Chart.js loaded from a CDN. The chart displays monthly sales data and demonstrates how to set up Chart.js in a browser without any build tools.</p>\n<h3>Features:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Uses the <strong>UMD version</strong> of Chart.js via CDN.</li>\n<li>Draws a simple <strong>line chart</strong> with labels and a dataset.</li>\n<li>Chart is fully <strong>responsive</strong> and includes a <strong>title</strong></li>\n</ul>\n",
      "type": "html"
    },
    {
      "code": "await scrib.loadScript(\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@4.4.0/dist/chart.umd.min.js\")",
      "status": "[4]<br><span style=\"font-size:8px\">3ms<span></span></span>",
